				<p>
					If you followed the tutorial step-by-step, you will be in the ruby main installation.
					You can check it by typing
<pre class="syntax brush-bash">
ruby -v
</pre>
				And you should see something like:
<pre class="syntax brush-ruby">

ruby 1.8.6 (2009-06-08 patchlevel 369) [universal-darwin9.0] #i run a mac, so this can change a little based on the os
</pre>
				If this is the output, then you are in the right path. If not, type "rvm system" and return back to the ruby main installation.
				</p>
				
				<p>
					After this we will going to fetch a script from the net, which will create for us an optimized and hacked version of rails just for us.
				</p>
				
				<p>
					For first, create a new directory, then enter in it
<pre class="syntax brush-bash">
mkdir my_app;
cd my_app;
</pre>
				</p>
				<p>
					Then, fetch this file from internet and execute it:
<pre class="syntax brush-bash">

curl -O http://appengine-jruby.googlecode.com/hg/demos/rails2/rails2_appengine.rb
ruby rails2_appengine.rb
</pre>
				</p>
				
				<p>
					After a minute or two, your application will be ready. Switch to the rvm jruby and fire the server!
<pre class="syntax brush-bash">
rvm jruby
./script/server.sh
</pre>
					Wait for loading and head your browser to "http://localhost:8080" and voil√†! Your JRuby on rails is done and ready to be deployed
